# skin-disorder-detection

## Abstract
This project focuses on the classification of Erythemato-Squamous Diseases (ESD) using supervised machine learning algorithms. The goal is to assist dermatologists in accurately diagnosing six common skin conditions by leveraging clinical and histopathological data.

**Stack:** 

This project utilizes standard technologies.


name: Admission_Prediction_-Linear_Regression-
description: Predicting graduate admission chances using linear regression with GRE, TOEFL, University Rating, SOP, LOR, CGPA, and Research. Explores data preprocessing, EDA, feature selection, regularization, polynomial features, and cross-validation to improve model accuracy. Polynomial features showed the best performance.
documentation:
# Admission_Prediction_-Linear_Regression-
Predicting graduate admission chances using linear regression with GRE, TOEFL, University Rating, SOP, LOR, CGPA, and Research. Explores data preprocessing, EDA, feature selection, regularization, polynomial features, and cross-validation to improve model accuracy. Polynomial features showed the best performance.
